casebody.data:
PEOPLE of the State of Michigan, Plaintiff-Appellee,
v.
Justin Michael BAILEY, Defendant-Appellant. SC: 157537
COA: 336685 Supreme Court of Michigan. November 21, 2018

Order

On order of the Court, the application for leave to appeal the February 27, 2018 judgment of the Court of Appeals is considered and, pursuant to MCR 7.305(H)(1), in lieu of granting leave to appeal, we VACATE the judgment of the Court of Appeals and we REMAND this case to the Court of Appeals for reconsideration in light of People v. Sharpe , 502 Mich. 313 , 918 N.W.2d 504 (2018).

We do not retain jurisdiction.
